Vice President Kamala Harris visited the Yokosuka Naval Base in Yokosuka, Japan, and addressed the sailors onboard the USS Howard. She expressed gratitude for their service and highlighted the importance of the US military in defending international law and maintaining peace and stability in the Indo-Pacific region. Harris also mentioned the growing threats posed by Russia, North Korea, and China, emphasizing the need to uphold the international rules-based order. She specifically addressed China's actions, including its challenges to freedom of the seas and provocations in the East China Sea, South China Sea, and Taiwan Strait. Harris reaffirmed the US commitment to Taiwan's self-defense and its support for a free and open Indo-Pacific. She concluded by thanking the sailors for their dedication and for standing up for freedom.